Blurb::
Supply a characteristic value to scale each reponse
Description::
Each entry in
\c primary_scales is a user-specified nonzero characteristic value
to scale each response.  

The argument may be of length 1 or the number of primary response
functions.  See the \c scaling keyword in the \ref method section for details on how to use this keyword.

